item.title: Help
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“RiiPiiNFtW, post:8, topic:430778”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=533454.msg3899768#msg3899768 date=1327642642]
The first problem is because in your items.cfg (or similar file) you put tabs instead of spaces, and so when the server tries to parse the item data, it’s reading more than the number (in your case it was “Dungeoneering” which isn’t a number).

The second is probably cause by a misplaced break;.
[/quote]Opposite actually. Spaces instead of tabs. :|[/quote]

I knew it was one of them. I wasn’t sure because I haven’t messed with a (poorly) organized config file like that in years. To prevent these types of errors now, I either use a binary file, or SQL queries.

Read full topic
